{{Infobox Person | name = Anne Worsley | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1588 | birth_place = | death_date = 1644 | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | other_names = | known_for = | education = | employer = | occupation = Prioress | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | parents = | relatives = | signature = | website = | footnotes = | nationality = English}}
'''Anne Worsley''' (1588 – 1644) was an [[England|English]] nun. She was the founding prioress of the English [[Carmelites|Carmelite]] convent in [[Antwerp]].
==Life== Worsley's parents were John and Eleanor Worsley who had lived on the [[Isle of Wight]] but the were persecuted because they were Roman Catholics and they went into exile. Anne decided on a religious life at the age of fifteen when she was living abroad. She decided to be a nun and opted for the Carmelites.<ref name="Hallett2013">{{cite book|author=Dr Nicky Hallett|title=The Senses in Religious Communities, 1600–1800: Early Modern ‘Convents of Pleasure’|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1jCGFKUxZNgC&pg=PT228|date=28 May 2013|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=978-1-4724-0137-3|pages=228–}}</ref> She was the founding prioress of the English Carmelite convent in [[Antwerp]] where her first novice was younger sister Theresa. She had visited Antwerp with her mentor [[Anne of Saint Bartholomew]] and other sources attribute the leadership of the Antwerp convent to her until she died in 1626.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://catholicsaints.info/blessed-anne-of-saint-bartholomew/|title=Blessed Anne of Saint Bartholomew|date=2009-06-07|work=CatholicSaints.Info|access-date=2018-02-26|language=en-US}}</ref>
Worsley died in 1644.<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Worsley, Anne [name in religion Anne of the Ascension] (1588–1644), founding prioress of the English Carmelite convent, Antwerp {{!}} Oxford Dictionary of National Biography|url=http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/10.1093/ref:odnb/9780198614128.001.0001/odnb-9780198614128-e-105826|language=en|doi=10.1093/ref:odnb/9780198614128.001.0001/odnb-9780198614128-e-105826}}</ref>
