{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Armand Pien''' (1920 &ndash; 2003) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] weatherman for 37 years. He was popular because his weather predictions were funny and somewhat cryptic.  

After he retired from national television he had a daily (Monday &ndash; Friday) weather talk on the East Flanders department of Belgium national radio. He did this until the Friday before his death; he died the following Monday.

In 2005 a small museum was opened in [[Hoeilaart]], [[Belgium]] dedicated to him.

==Quotes==
* ''"An autumn without storm is like a woman without curves."''
* ''"After rain there will always be sunshine."''

